definition.value: The ideology that being cisgender is normal; i.e. the assumption that a person's gender identity always matches their sex as assigned at birth.
The ideology that being cisgender and heterosexual is the societal norm; the intersection of cisnormativity and heteronormativity.
Ideologies which conform to societal expectations of masculinity or understandings of what "normal" masculinity should look like in a given society.
Any of various kinds of normativity based on romantic or sociosexual orientations or statuses.
The ideology that romance is tied to traditional ideas of sexual activity, monogamy, and/or marriage and that romantic love is not possible outside of these traditional boundaries.
The ideology that romantic and sexual relationships can only occur, or are only normal, between two monogamous partners.
Any of various kinds of normativity based on sexuality.
The ideology that heterosexuality is normative or default and that sexual and marital relationships "fit" between men and women.

The privileging of heteronormative ideals and constructs onto LGBTQIA+ culture and identity. It is predicated on the assumption that the norms and values of heterosexuality should be replicated and performed among homosexual people.

A sex for clinical use value in which stereotypically or statistically "female" values apply to an individual in a given medical context, such as for a procedure, process, algorithm, hormone level, genetic composition, organ inventory, etc.

A sex for clinical use value in which stereotypically or statistically "male" values apply to an individual in a given medical context, such as for a procedure, process, algorithm, hormone level, genetic composition, organ inventory, etc.

A sex for clinical use value which contains some specified value or values that apply to an individual in a given medical context, such as for a procedure, process, algorithm, hormone level, genetic composition, organ inventory, etc.
A sex for clinical use value in which the stereotypical or statistical known values do not apply, cannot be determined, or are not sufficient for determination of a another value.

A widespread feeling of fear, often an irrational one, that some evil person or thing threatens the values, interests, or well-being of a community or society. It is "the process of arousing social concern over an issue," usually perpetuated by moral entrepreneurs and the mass media, and exacerbated by politicians and lawmakers.

A particular part of the wider "Satanic panic" that occurred primarily during the 1980s and early 1990s, and featured charges against day-care providers accused of committing several forms of child abuse, including Satanic ritual abuse. A prominent case in Kern County, California, United States, first publicized the issue of day-care sexual abuse, and the issue figured prominently in news coverage for almost a decade. The Kern County case was followed by cases elsewhere in the United States, as well as Canada, New Zealand, Brazil, and various European countries.

Racism based upon one's ancestry as supposedly related to the "racial" content of their blood. Such racism was amplified and even codified in law in the United States as the 'one-drop rule' and its derivatives.
A finding which is sexual in nature.
Typically, a person nineteen years old or younger who has either given birth to or electing to parent a child with which there is some relationship.
Parenthood in which a parent is nineteen years old or younger.
Typically, a person nineteen years old or younger who has given birth to a child with which there is some relationship.
A person who is associated with sex work in some sense.
An individual who engages with a sex worker for some form of sexual services.
High-risk sexual behavior during the period of adolescence.
Organizations organized by subject of focus.
Organizations organized by type, such as associations, collectives, cooperatives, trade unions, etc.
An organization where a specified activity is concentrated. A place where a particular activity or service is concentrated.
Any of various organizations which act as repositories for particular kinds of documentation.
A healthcare facility that provides comprehensive, high-quality primary health care services for children.
A center and resource for individuals going through any of various crises, typically related to mental health.
An organization, building or complex that promotes culture and arts. Cultural centers can be neighborhood community arts organizations, private facilities, government-sponsored, or activist-run.
Any of various organizations which act as repositories for documentation related to, or otherwise concerning, HIV/AIDS.
Any of various organizations which act as repositories for documentation about LGBTQIA+ persons, or concerning such persons.
A center which provides advice regarding health or raising awareness about any of various health issues.
A health center which treats pregnant people and very young children.
A center which aims to provide access to the workforce and opportunities for employment.
Any of various centers which offer advice.
A center which offers legal information, advice, referrals, and, in some cases, brief services.
Any location used for detention, a process whereby a state or private citizen lawfully holds a person by removing their freedom or liberty at that time.
Any of various detention centers typically designed for adults, or in which a majority adult population is in detention.
Any of various detention centers typically designed for youth, or in which a majority youth population is in detention.
Any of various detention centers typically designed for immigrants, or in which a majority immigrant population is in detention.
A center which offers legal information, advice, referrals, and, in some cases, brief services, specifically for youth.
Any of various organizations which act as repositories for documentation about men, or concerning men.
Any of various computer networks used commonly with bulletin board systems.

A computer server running software that allows users to connect to the system using a terminal program. Once logged in, the user can perform functions such as uploading and downloading software and data, reading news and bulletins, and exchanging messages with other users through public message boards and sometimes via direct chatting.
Any of various policies regarding human rights.
Any of various policies regarding LGBTQ rights.
An infection that is caused by Chlamydia trachomatis.
An infectious disease that is caused by Chlamydia trachomatis.
